quran[88]{c,v,t}:
  38,1,"бєҐ√£d. By the Quran, full of reminders"
  38,2,"ЋєThis is the truth,ЋЇ yet the disbelievers are ЋєentrenchedЋЇ in arrogance and opposition"
  38,3,"ЋєImagineЋЇ how many peoples We destroyed before them, and they cried out when it was too late to escape"
  38,4,"Now, the pagans are astonished that a warner has come to them from among themselves.¬†And the disbelievers say, вАЬThis is a magician, a total liar"
  38,5,"Has he reduced ЋєallЋЇ the gods to One God? Indeed, this is something totally astonishing.вАЭ"
  38,6,"The chiefs among them went forth saying, вАЬCarry on, and stand firm in devotion to your gods. Certainly this is just a scheme Ћєfor powerЋЇ"
  38,7,We have never heard of this in the previous faith.¬†This is nothing but a fabrication
  38,8,"Has the Reminder been revealed ЋєonlyЋЇ to him out of Ћєall ofЋЇ us?вАЭ In fact, they are ЋєonlyЋЇ in doubt of My ЋєrevealedЋЇ Reminder.¬†In fact, Ћєthey do so becauseЋЇ they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ they possess the treasuries of the mercy of your LordвАФthe Almighty, the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ"
  38,10,"Or Ћєis it becauseЋЇ the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between belongs to them? Let them then climb their way Ћєto heaven, if their claim is trueЋЇ"
  38,11,This is just another ЋєenemyЋЇ force bound for defeat out there
  38,12,"Before them, the people of Noah denied Ћєthe truthЋЇ, as did вАЩ√Вd, Pharaoh of the mighty structures"
  38,13,"Tham√їd, the people of Lot, and the residents of the Forest.¬†These were ЋєallЋЇ enemy forces"
  38,14,"Each rejected their messenger, so My punishment was justified"
  38,15,These ЋєpagansЋЇ are awaiting nothing but a single Blast that cannot be stopped
  38,16,"They say ЋєmockinglyЋЇ, вАЬOur Lord! Hasten for us our share Ћєof the punishmentЋЇ before the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,17,"Be patient ЋєO ProphetЋЇ with what they say. And remember Our servant, David, the man of strength. Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,18,We truly subjected the mountains to hymn ЋєOur praisesЋЇ along with him in the evening and after sunrise
  38,19,"And ЋєWe subjectedЋЇ the birds, flocking together. All turned to him Ћєechoing his hymnsЋЇ"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingship, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment"
  38,21,"Has the story of the two plaintiffs, who scaled the Ћєwall of DavidвАЩsЋЇ sanctuary, reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ"
  38,22,"When they came into DavidвАЩs presence, he was startled by them. They said, вАЬHave no fear. ЋєWe are merelyЋЇ two in a dispute: one of us has wronged the other. So judge between us with truthвАФdo not go beyond ЋєitЋЇвАФand guide us to the right way"
  38,23,"This is my brother.¬†He has ninety-nine sheep while I have ЋєonlyЋЇ one. ЋєStillЋЇ he asked me to give it up to him, overwhelming me with ЋєhisЋЇ argument.вАЭ"
  38,24,"David ЋєeventuallyЋЇ ruled, вАЬHe has definitely wronged you in demanding Ћєto addЋЇ your sheep to his. And certainly many partners wrong each other, except those who believe and do goodвАФbut how few are they!вАЭ Then David realized that We had tested him so he asked for his LordвАЩs forgiveness, fell down in prostration, and turned Ћєto Him in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,25,So We forgave that for him. And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,26,"ЋєWe instructed him:ЋЇ вАЬO David! We have surely made you an authority in the land, so judge between people with truth. And do not follow ЋєyourЋЇ desires or they will lead you astray from AllahвАЩs Way. Surely those who go astray from AllahвАЩs Way will suffer a severe punishment for neglecting the Day of Reckoning.вАЭ"
  38,27,We have not created the heavens and earth and everything in between without purposeвАФas the disbelievers think. So woe to the disbelievers because of the Fire
  38,28,Or should We treat those who believe and do good like those who make mischief throughout the land? Or should We treat the righteous like the wicked
  38,29,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a blessed Book which We have revealed to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ so that they may contemplate its verses, and people of reason may be mindful"
  38,30,"And We blessed David with SolomonвАФwhat an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,31,"ЋєRememberЋЇ when the well-trained, swift horses were paraded before him in the evening"
  38,32,"He then proclaimed, вАЬI am truly in love with ЋєtheseЋЇ fine things out of remembrance for Allah,вАЭ until they went out of sight"
  38,33,"ЋєHe ordered,ЋЇ вАЬBring them back to me!вАЭ Then he began to rub down their legs and necks"
  38,34,"And indeed, We tested Solomon, placing a ЋєdeformedЋЇ body on his throne,¬†then he turned Ћєto Allah in repentanceЋЇ"
  38,35,"He prayed, вАЬMy Lord! Forgive me, and grant me an authority that will never be matched by anyone after me. You are indeed the Giver Ћєof all bountiesЋЇ.вАЭ"
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind, blowing gently at his command to wherever he pleased"
  38,37,And ЋєWe subjected to himЋЇ every builder and diver¬†of the jinn
  38,38,and others bound together in chains
  38,39,"ЋєAllah said,ЋЇ вАЬThis is Our gift, so give or withhold Ћєas you wishЋЇ, never to be called to account.вАЭ"
  38,40,And he will indeed have Ћєa status ofЋЇ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he cried out to his Lord, вАЬSatan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.вАЭ"
  38,42,"ЋєWe responded,ЋЇ вАЬStomp your foot: ЋєnowЋЇ here is a cool Ћєand refreshingЋЇ spring for washing and drinking.вАЭ"
  38,43,"And We gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for people of reason"
  38,44,"ЋєAnd We said to him,ЋЇ вАЬTake in your hand a bundle of grass, and strike Ћєyour wifeЋЇ with it, and do not break your oath.вАЭ¬†We truly found him patient. What an excellent servant Ћєhe wasЋЇ! Indeed, he ЋєconstantlyЋЇ turned Ћєto AllahЋЇ"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants: Abraham, Isaac, and JacobвАФthe men of strength and insight"
  38,46,We truly chose them for the honour of proclaiming the Hereafter
  38,47,And in Our sight they are truly among the chosen and the finest
  38,48,"Also remember Ishmael, Elisha, and в±Ђul-Kifl.¬†All are among the best"
  38,49,This is ЋєallЋЇ a reminder. And the righteous will certainly have an honourable destination
  38,50,"the Gardens of Eternity, whose gates will be open for them"
  38,51,"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink"
  38,52,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and equal age
  38,53,This is what you are promised for the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,This is indeed Our provision that will never end
  38,55,That is that. And the transgressors will certainly have the worst destination
  38,56,"Hell, where they will burn. What an evil place to rest"
  38,57,"Let them then taste this: boiling water and ЋєoozingЋЇ pus"
  38,58,and other torments of the same sort
  38,59,"ЋєThe misleaders will say to one another,ЋЇ вАЬHere is a crowd Ћєof followersЋЇ being thrown in with us. They are not welcome, ЋєforЋЇ they ЋєtooЋЇ will burn in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,60,"The followers will respond, вАЬNo! You are not welcome! You brought this upon us. What an evil place for settlement!вАЭ"
  38,61,"Adding, вАЬOur Lord! Whoever brought this upon us, double their punishment in the Fire.вАЭ"
  38,62,"The tyrants will ask Ћєone anotherЋЇ, вАЬBut why do we not see those we considered to be lowly"
  38,63,Were we wrong in mocking them Ћєin the worldЋЇ?¬†Or do our eyes ЋєjustЋЇ fail to see them Ћєin the FireЋЇ?вАЭ
  38,64,This dispute between the residents of the Fire will certainly come to pass
  38,65,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI am only a warner. And there is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except AllahвАФthe One, the Supreme"
  38,66,"ЋєHe is theЋЇ Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in betweenвАФthe Almighty, Most Forgiving.вАЭ"
  38,67,"Say, вАЬThis ЋєQuranЋЇ is momentous news"
  38,68,from which you ЋєpagansЋЇ are turning away.вАЭ
  38,69,"ЋєAnd say,ЋЇ вАЬI had no knowledge of the highest assembly Ћєin heavenЋЇ when they differed Ћєconcerning AdamЋЇ"
  38,70,What is revealed to me is that I am only sent with a clear warning.вАЭ
  38,71,"ЋєRemember, O ProphetЋЇ when your Lord said to the angels, вАЬI am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ЋєcreationЋЇ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.вАЭ"
  38,73,So the angels prostrated all togetherвАФ
  38,74,"but not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"Allah asked, вАЬO Ibl√Ѓs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ЋєjustЋЇ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?вАЭ"
  38,76,"He replied, вАЬI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.вАЭ"
  38,77,"Allah commanded, вАЬThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.вАЭ
  38,79,"Satan appealed, вАЬMy Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  38,80,"Allah said, вАЬYou will be delayed"
  38,81,until the appointed Day.вАЭ
  38,82,"Satan said, вАЬBy Your Glory! I will certainly mislead them all"
  38,83,except Your chosen servants among them.вАЭ
  38,84,"Allah concluded, вАЬThe truth isвАФand I ЋєonlyЋЇ say the truthвАФ"
  38,85,"I will surely fill up Hell with you and whoever follows you from among them, all together.вАЭ"
  38,86,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI do not ask you for any reward for this ЋєQuranЋЇ, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.вАЭ